Password Policy's
-change default passwords
-Avoid person information
-Avoid real words
-Long is strong
-Increase compedxity
-Don't use stick notes
-Update passwords
-Don't reuse password
-Use a password manager(Key pass)

Privileged User Agreement PLA
-This outlines guidelines, rules, restrictions, and consequences of violations

Anti-Malware Policy
-Rules for using anti-malware software and policies for installing programs, sharing files, using external storage.
-Every computer should have anti-malware + cleaning software
-An anti-malware team should focus on maintaining malware program detects malware
-Users should know what to do in case their anti-malware progra detects malware
-Users should be prohibited from installing any unauthorized software on their systems
-Mobile device managment(MDM) can secure  
